Twenty-two women in South Africa contracted HIV during gel trials to prevent infection.
Male circumcision trials also show promise in reducing HIV risk.
Studies on herpes drugs like valacyclovir suggest potential for controlling HIV spread.
XDR tuberculosis poses a significant threat, especially in South African HIV patients.
HIV-related dementia is a growing concern in sub-Saharan Africa.
Malawi is working on laws to protect against deliberate HIV infection.
British research indicates herpes drugs could help control HIV transmission.
These findings highlight the ongoing challenges and potential breakthroughs in the fight against HIV/AIDS.
